I finally beat the game!!!!! (Golden Deer, Maddening)

It was extremely tough but I really enjoyed the story and gameplay. Lysethia was indeed my best unit throughout the whole game. 
With her staff Thyrsus and couple of buff abilities, she became the most reliable glass cannon in my team. 
Not to mention that she cleared nearly half of the units in the final mission.

Here is my regular roster for this level
Hilda - Great Knight
Berna - Bow Knight
Dorothea - Gremory
Ingrid - Falcon Knight
Lysethia - Dark Knight
Marianne - Holy Knight
Mercedes - Bishop
Petra - Assasin
Annette - Gremory
Claude - Barbossa
Byleth - Enlightened One

Yes it was an all-star harem team paradise lol

I think attack range and mobility are most important in this game. I really spammed Lysethia's 'sniping' which helped me clear missions in a breeze. I even gave her all the magic boosting items so that she can become a hyper-carry mage.

I love this game and cannot wait to play a more harder level of this one. Hope there are some more side stories in the DLC!

caption.text: Tetris to klasyk. Gra logiczna zaprojektowana przez Aleksieja Pażytnowa, która powstała  w 1984 roku. Wydawać się mogło, że z nic więcej już z tej gry nie można wyciągnąć. Tymczasem w 2019 roku na Nintendo Switch pojawił się Tetris99, czyli połączenie znanego wszystkim klasyka z fomułą battle royale. w rozgrywce bierze udział 99 graczy i zwycięzca partii jest tylko jeden gracz. Ta gra to dowód na to, że wiele jeszcze w branży przed nami i nawet największe klasyki mogą powrócić w nowej formie. #tetris #tetris99 #nintendo #nintendoswitch #nintendogames #battleroyale #consolegames #videogames #multiplayer #blackandwhite #gamerlife #gamer #gamerstuff #graczzpolski #gracz #nintendoexclusive #gaming #switch #gameaddict #retrogames #gamergeek

caption.text: "✨Endschädigungs Gewinnspiel✨“ Aufgabe :Schnappt euch auf SO/MO/US/UM ein beliebiges Pikachu und gibt es den Namen :" Flare. TV“ Jetzt der wichtigste Punkt! Gibt in der GTS Gavalanzas 1-10 Geschlecht Männlich ein! Das ist ein sehr wichtiger Punkt! Da die GTS ein öffentlicher Service ist,muss aber damit gerechnet werden, dass euch das Pikachu vor der Nase weggetauscht werden kann! Versucht es dann bitte nochmal! Seit aber nicht enttäuscht, falls ihr kein Glück habt! Nicht jeder kann gewinnen und ich habe nur drei Exemplare die zu Verfügung stehen! Jetzt noch ein sehr sehr wichtiger Punkt! Schreibt unter dem Post hier, wie ihr im Spiel heißt! Damit ich euch identifizieren kann! Das Gewinnspiel wird ohne Vorankündigung beendet! Nach Ende des Gewinnspiel werde ich hier einen Beitrag posten, wie ich im Spiel als Trainer Flare. TV euch auf dem Festival - Plaza anspreche! Das ist nach dem Tausch möglich, wenn ihr den Tauschpartner im Schloss anspricht! Dieser Schritt gilt aber nur für mich um die Leute die hier mitmachen zu identifizieren! Also schnapp euch ein Pikachu und legt es für 1-10 Gavalanzas Männlich ab! Flare.TV als Namen nicht vergessen! Viel Spaß! P. S für alle die mitmachen wollen, Namen wie ihr im Spiel heißt hier drunter posten(nur für Spiele der sieben Generationen) ✨✨✨#shinyhunter #gts #pikachu #trade #pokemongo #gamefreak #nintendo #nintendoswitch @trainerin.laura @_pokelife_ #gaming #GameStop #germany #Pokemonsunandmoon #usum #gewinnspiel #pokemongo🎮 #shiny #nintendoswitch #pokemonartwork #pokemonmemes #nintendoswitchlite #instagram #youtube #facebook #pokemonapp

caption.text:
Dragon Quest XI: Echoes of an Elusive Age tells a captivating tale of a hunted hero and is the long-awaited role-playing game from series creator Yuji Horii, character designer Akira Toriyama and composer Koichi Sugiyama. While it is the eleventh mainline entry in the critically acclaimed series, Dragon Quest XI is a completely standalone experience that features entirely new characters, a beautifully detailed world, finely tuned turn-based combat, and an immersive story that will appeal to long-time fans and franchise newcomers alike. A young man, about to participate in his village's coming of age ceremony, travels to a Sacred Stone alongside his childhood friend. After a series of unexpected events, this intrepid adventurer learns he is the reincarnation of a legendary hero from a forgotten age. The young hero sets forth into an unknown world on a journey to unravel the mystery of his past... but the welcome he receives is far from warm. Upon revealing his identity to the King, the hero is branded as "The Dark spawn" and hunted by a relentless army. Fleeing from his pursuers, the hero assembles a band of endearing adventurers who believe he is actually The Luminary reborn. The hero and his newfound companions embark on a quest that will take them across continents and over vast oceans as they learn of an ominous threat facing the world. 
Developer: Square Enix
Genre(s): Role-Playing, Japanese-Style

caption.text:
Pssst, want to hear a secret? I think DQB2 might be my GOTY!! 😱

I'm sure you'll all be pleased to know that ya gurl finished a game for once! That's right. After 75+ hours of epic game play, I finally finished the main storyline of DQB2. And what a ride it was!

I don't even know how to put into words how much I love this game. But, I think 75+ hours is a pretty decent indication. And I really wanted to finish it before Link's Awakening came out, but I underestimated just how big this game is. It's BIG. Totally worth the asking price, if you were wondering. In fact, they should absolutely charge more for that shiz.

Also, does anyone else make notes about what items are required for quests? Just me? I found it super helpful, especially when I was working on multiple rooms at once - this memory ain't what it used to be!

Now, it's your turn to tell me a secret! What's your GOTY so far?!

caption.text: السلام عليكم لعبتنا اليوم هي (أوفيركوكيد ٢)قد نزلت لعبة سنة ٢٠١٨ على جميع الاجهزة من بلاي استيشن ٤ وإكس بوكس و نينتدو سويچ. قصة لعبة في مملكة بصلة يأتي ملك بصل يجيب العيد في مملكة ويظهر زومبي توست يأتي دورك بان تقدم طلبات المطلوبة في مطابخ مجنونة وهنا ممتعة في لعبة. نظام لعبة هي تطبخ طلبات موجودة في منيو ومطابخ فيها تحدي مستمر وكل مرحلة تختلف مطبخ من آخر وبصراحة هي ممتعة جدا عندما تلعبها واحد او ٤ في نفس الغرفة او مع أصدقائك اولاين تعتبر لعبة من اكثر العاب ناجحة من ناحية تحدي جماعي جميل وممتعة وبصراحة لا تطوف اقيمها ٨/١٠

caption.text:
🇺🇸 I'm back! Holidays are always short... I leave here one of my acquisitions during these days: Moto GP 19. Every year the current Moto GP game for all platforms is sold on the circuit, and this year, after several years playing it on PS4, I have opted to try the Nintendo Switch one. I must say that the jump in image quality from PS4 to Switch is quite noticeable, but the rest is equally satisfactory if you like this kind of games. I liked it a lot and I have hooked like every year, but the only downside, in my opinion, is that the one player campaign is still very little personalized, it would be appreciated to interact more with your pilot, doing things like talking to the press or being able to customize more aspects of skills or character. Do you like sports games? What are your favorites? 👾
_______________________
🇪🇸 ¡He vuelto! Que cortas se hacen siempre las vacaciones... os dejo por aquí una de mis adquisiciones durante estos días: Moto GP 19. Cada año se vende en el mismo circuito el juego de Moto GP vigente para todas las plataformas, y este año, después de varios años jugándolo en PS4, me he decantado por probar el de Nintendo Switch. Debo decir que el salto en calidad de imagen de PS4 a Switch se nota bastante, pero el resto es igualmente satisfactorio si te gustan esta clase de juegos. Me ha gustado bastante y me he viciado como cada año, pero la única pega, a mi parecer, es que la campaña de un jugador sigue siendo muy poco personalizada, se agradecería poder interactuar más con tu piloto, haciendo cosas como hablar con la prensa o poder personalizar más aspectos de las habilidades o el carácter. ¿A vosotros os gustan los juegos de deportes? ¿Cuáles son vuestros favoritos? 👾 .

caption.text:
One of Nintendo’s most successful franchises, “Mario Kart Tour”, is now available for everyone to play on their smartphones.
.
While it will be a similar gameplay to the Switch, some of its controls and features will be optimised for mobile devices. For example. The multiplayer option will not be available for the meantime but it is expected to be added later on as an in-app purchase option.
.
A test version of the game developed with partner DeNA Co Ltd featured in-game payment mechanics including gacha where players pay to receive random rewards — such as rare drivers and karts. “It’s going to be a challenge to apply Japanese-style gacha mechanics in the West,” said Michael Pachter, analyst at Wedbush Securities, who sees Mario Kart Tour struggling to hold players’ interest long enough to sustain in-game spending.
It also remains to be seen whether Nintendo will be able to square the use of gacha with its famous family-friendly image.
.
But for the meantime, the app is now available to download on the App Store and the Google Play Store and is totally free to play! Enjoy Nintendo fans! .
.

caption.text:
From the groundbreaking Game & Watch to the original Game Boy brick to the strangely enticing dual-screened DS, Nintendo has always made hardware you want to hold in your hands and play with. It’s a company that understands gaming on the go.
 Things have come full circle with the $199 Switch Lite, which hits stores starting on September 20th. It’s a smaller and cheaper version of the device that cuts out a core feature: you can’t hook up a Switch Lite to your TV. It’s designed exclusively for playing in handheld mode. With the original Switch, Nintendo proved that games didn’t have to be designed around hardware, and that with the right device, you could enjoy the same game in a variety of places and situations. With the Switch Lite, the company has proved something very different: it can still build one hell of a handheld.

GOOD STUFF
Streamlined, sturdier design
Improved battery life
Excellent directional pad

BAD STUFF
Can’t connect to a TV
Some games aren’t compatible out of the box
No kickstand

At its most basic, the Switch Lite really is just a smaller Switch. It has a 5.5-inch touchscreen, compared to the original’s 6.2-inch display, and it’s overall much tinier. The Switch Lite clocks in at 3.6 inches high, 8.2 inches long, and 0.55 inches deep. It’s extremely light, at a minuscule 0.61 pounds, so it’s a lot easier on your arms if you want to play some Zelda in bed. The controller layout is largely the same, and it has the same slots for game cards and a microSD card. And yes, there’s a headphone jack. (Though, if you thought the lack of detachable controllers would mean Bluetooth headphone support, you’re out of luck). It also runs the exact same, fairly basic operating system as the base Switch, and Nintendo says it has three to seven hours of battery life. That’s proved largely true during my time with it so far. I tested a lot of different kinds of games and generally had to recharge every four or five hours.$300 price

A while ago, when my family and I went to the store and I was a bit younger, I wanted to get a drink at the cafe in the store. @black_cat_h2yk gave me some change and some small bills while she was checking out. So I walked over to the cafe counter with an orange drink from the fridge they kept by the counter. The lady that was working gave me my total, about 2 or 3 dollars and I stuck out my hand, opened it up and dropped a fist full of change on the counter. I looked at her and with a dead serious expression and tone asked "is it okay if I pay with this?" It was a lot of change, mostly pennies. A look of absolute horror crossed her face for a second then she smiled sweetly and said "of course" so I stuck out my other hand with the Bill's in it and said "good, but I'd rather pay with this." She looked surprised, and I could almost hear her sigh with relief that she wouldn't have to count all that change... -
-

caption.text:
//TAKING A BREAK//
~Continue or Quit~

Hi everyone!

I’m most likely taking a break from Instagram.
I did the same thing a year ago and it felt good.
This summer I also took a step back for a few weeks to celebrate my vacation.
•
This time however, I actually might be closing this account. I’m still not sure about that yet, but it’s been crossing my mind for some time now.
•
For me, I think I can spent my time better and I don’t want to sent out wrong signals towards my children. Sure, gaming is a hobby, but let’s keep it that way.
•
Eventhough I don’t have many followers at all it still feels a bit weird. With some of you I often have short, but nice contacts and I really enjoy your posts!
•
Point is, I love sharing content with you guys. Interacting and letting you know what I’m playing.
But sometimes, no, often, I’m not really sure why I keep on going.
Of course, every know and then I get a new game, post a picture and letting you know what I think about it.
Other than that, I don’t consider myself a collector. I buy specific games because I think I’ll enjoy them. Not to mention merchandise.
(I don’t have a lot).
So, not much variety to post.
•
I know it’s not a competition, and I really don’t feel that way. But I do feel that sometimes I take a lot of time to shoot some photos and basically spent a lot of time on my phone.
Just like I’m doing right now, writing this caption.
I can’t imagine how much effort it takes and how much pressure there is for accounts with thousands of followers. I have mad respect for you!
•
So, reducing phone time for me that is!
•
I won’t log into this account for at least a month, starting October 1. After that I’ll see what happens.
•
I will keep on playing videogames.
I still have lots to play, continue or replay!
•
I do have a private account but I only post once, or maybe twice a month. So that’s no big deal.
I also have the account: breathofthewildstagram, but haven’t posted in ages because it’s been a while since I’ve played BotW.
•
I will be back, but for now, thank you so much for your support and if I do decide to quit this account, I’ll be sure letting you guys know.
•
And if you haven’t already, add my Switch Friendcode
#amiibo #nintendoswitch #alaingamers #abudhabigamers #dubaigamers
This year I had a super great time playing #FinalFantasyVII, #FinalFantasyVIII and #FinalFantasyIX on #NintendoSwitch.

.

caption.text:
》„Die Stimme eines Kindes, egal wie ehrlich oder aufrichtig, ist bedeutungslos für jene, die verlernt haben zuzuhören.“ (Albus Dumbledore)《
Für mich gehört im Herbst & Winter eines immer unbedingt dazi: Harry Potter lesen, spielen und gucken. 😅
Ich weiß noch ganz genau, wie ich damals den ersten Band zu Weihnachten bekam und eine lange Liebe begann.
Die Geschichten, die Abenteuer, die Weisheiten von Dumbledore... all das hat mich in meiner Jugend  und bis heute geprägt.
Ich hoffe sehr, dass ich diese Liebe an meine Tochter weitergeben kann. 😍
.
Wie alt wart ihr, als eure Liebe für diese Welt entfachte? Oder bist du zufällig gar kein Fan? 😱😅
.
🇬🇧 How old were  you, Ehen your love to Harry Potter begun?
.
